# dotfiles-Gentoo/gentoo/package.use.example
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# USE flags are Gentoo's whole point: they gate optional features at COMPILE time.
# This file is a REVIEW-AND-COPY template, not something bootstrap applies. Put
# the lines you want into /etc/portage/package.use/ (it can be a single file or a
# directory of files). After editing, re-emerge the affected package, or run a
# world update with --newuse:  sudo emerge -auvDN --newuse @world
#
# See a package's available flags first:   equery uses <category/name>
#                                           emerge -pv <category/name>
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Most of this dotfiles stack builds fine on default USE. A few you MIGHT want:

# fzf — enable shell/editor integration helpers if you use them:
# app-shells/fzf vim

# git — build the libsecret credential helper (then point os.gitconfig at it):
# dev-vcs/git -tk -webdav

# neovim — lean it out a touch (drop the GUI bits you won't use in a terminal):
# app-editors/neovim -gtk

# Global flags you'd more likely set in /etc/portage/make.conf, not here, e.g.:
#   USE="-X wayland git" CPU_FLAGS_X86="..."   (run `cpuid2cpuflags` to get yours)
